  "birth_place": "Hamburg",
  "description": "德國哲學家（1891–1953）",
  "bio": "漢斯·賴興巴赫（德語：Hans Reichenbach；1891年9月26日—1953年4月9日），德國哲學家。出生於漢堡，賴興巴赫是科學哲學的先驅、邏輯實證主義(也稱作新實證主義或者邏輯經驗主義)的支持者。他於1928年在柏林創立了經驗哲學學會（Gesellschaft für empirische Philosophie，柏林小組的前身）。",
  "bio_source": "zhwiki",
  "description_en": "German–American philosopher",
  "bio_en": "Hans Reichenbach (; German: [ˈʁaɪçənbax]; September 26, 1891 – April 9, 1953) was a leading philosopher of science, educator, and proponent of logical empiricism. He founded the Gesellschaft für empirische Philosophie (Society for Empirical Philosophy) in Berlin in 1928, also known as the \"Berlin Circle\". Carl Gustav Hempel, Richard von Mises, David Hilbert and Kurt Grelling all became members of the Berlin Circle.\nIn 1930, Reichenbach and Rudolf Carnap became editors of the journal Erkenntnis.",
  "bio_en_source": "enwiki"
}